memberOrga:
Our members decided to join bean having realised that the European agricultural competitiveness could be improved through better access to nutrients. Better access to nutrients means a better quality of fertilisers, secured availability and a fair price compared to other major agricultural regions with whom European farmers compete. Nitrogen and phosphate fertilisers are , for instance, 10% more expensive in Western Europe that in Brazil or South East Asia. New members are always welcome. Find out here (soon) why you should join ABEAN today! Our members are European stakeholders representing:&#xd;
&#xd;
- 700 blenders and complex fertilizer plants;&#xd;
- 3,000 fertilizer distributors and cooperatives;&#xd;
- 1,000 farmers;&#xd;
- Logistic operators working with over 10 different &#xd;
  European ports.
